The paper focuses on a neural architecture that combines vision and natural language, specifically for the task of visual commonsense reasoning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). However, given the emphasis on language and the use of transformers, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant due to the use of computer vision and machine learning techniques.
